race.comment: THE ENCHANTER (3) is an honest conveyance who is yet to miss the top-five in eight starts to date and will be high on confidence following a last-start victory over this track and trip. Winning rider McMurray sticks in the saddle and again gets the benefit of his 3kg claim. Ticks plenty of boxes. SYNERGY IN MOTION (13) may have suffered from the dreaded second-up syndrome at the latest effort but go on the solid win over this course and distance when resuming. Can bounce right back. Former NSW galloper FIRST MISSION (5) is having his first run for the new stable but should find this assignment easier than what he faced down south. May run a race while fresh. ENCUBIERTO (4) is a last-start winner who shouldn't be underestimated.
